                                <p style=" font-size: 11pt; margin-top: -10px; ">Observe that most of the misconceptions interviewers make relate to the first impression. Reiterate to the candidates that making a good first impression is as important as having the right knowledge and skills for the job. </p>
                                <ul> Some of the Common misconceptions interviewers make are:
                                    <li>‘A person with scuffed shoes is likely to be disorganized.’</li>
                                    <li>‘Wearing a red tie is a sign of confidence.’ </li>
                                    <li>‘No Eye Contact. I am sure he is hiding something.’</li>
                                    <li>‘I have been in this business for a long time. I know a good candidate when I see one.’</li>
                                    <li>‘That’s a firm hand shake. I know he is right for the job.’ </li>   
                                </ul>
                                <ul> The following statements are not misconceptions:
